<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sonics Sign Guard Fred Vinson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- The Seattle SuperSonics plucked 6-foot-4 guard  
Fred Vinson out of their summer league team and signed him Thursday 
to a one-year contract, the team announced. 
</P>
<P>
	Vinson, 28, averaged 15 points per game and shot 45 percent from  
3-point range for the Sonics' summer league teams in Long Beach and 
Boston. 
</P>
<P>
	``Fred was very impressive in last year's training camp and  
almost made the team,'' coach Paul Westphal said. ``But because of 
the lockout we didn't get a sufficient chance to evaluate him. He 
excelled on our summer league team and was one of the best outside 
shooters we saw this summer. We think he really has a chance to 
help us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Vinson played two years at Georgia Tech after transferring from  
a junior college, then signed as a free agent with the Atlanta 
Hawks in 1994. After playing five games with the Hawks, he spent 
time with the CBA franchise in Mexico City and played in Europe. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
