<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 15:00:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Silverbulletday Debuts at Saratoga </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Silverbulletday, owner Mike  
Pegram's summer cooler, will try to stretch her winning streak 
against other 3-year-old fillies to 10 on Saturday in the Alabama 
at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
	She was made the 1-2 early favorite Thursday to succeed against  
six rivals in the 1 1/4-mile Grade I stakes. 
</P>
<P>
	``Anytime I watch her race, I get chills,'' Pegram said from  
California. ``It's really a thrill.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Silverbulletday, the champion 2-year-old filly of 1998 when she  
won six of seven starts, including the Breeders' Cup Juvenile 
Fillies. Her loss was a fourth-place finish in the Del Mar 
Futurity, won by Excellent Meeting, her Bob Baffert-trained 
stablemate. 
</P>
<P>
	Her only loss this year was a seventh-place finish in the  
1 1/2-mile Belmont Stakes June 5, her only start against males. 
</P>
<P>
	She was in contention until fading the stretch.  
</P>
<P>
	``I thought it was a pretty good performance,'' said Jerry  
Bailey, who didn't use the filly when it became apparent she 
couldn't win. ``The number of lengths she got beat (10 1/2) are 
deceiving.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In her last race, Silverbulletday won the 1 1-8 Monmouth Oaks on  
July 18. 
</P>
<P>
	``A horse like Silverbulletday is one that you run into once in  
a lifetime,'' Pegram said. ``I really can't express in words the 
kind of trip she's taken me on since she started racing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	It is Silverbulletday who will have to take Pegram to the  
winner's circle on Breeders' Cup Day Nov. 6 because his Real Quiet, 
also trained by Baffert, is out for the year with a cracked leg 
bone. He was to run the Classic. Silverbulletday's goal is the 
Distaff. 
</P>
<P>
	Silverbulletday's main rival in $400,000 Alabama appears to be  
3-1 On a Soapbox, winner of two of three starts this year, 
including the 1 1/2-mile Coaching Club American Oaks July 24 at 
Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	The field in post-position order is Gandria, Shane Sellers; Back  
In Shape, Jose Espinoza; On a Soapbox, Robby Albarado; Brushed 
Halory, Eddie Martin; Adam's Time, Jorge Chavez; Silverbulletday, 
Bailey, and Strolling Belle, Mike Smith. 
</P>
<P>
	Each starter will carry 121 pounds.  
</P>
<P>
	Post time for the 119th Alabama, the oldest filly race in the  
country, is 4:45 p.m. EDT. ESPN will televise from 4 p.m. to 5 p.m. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
