<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Will Clark Misses 5th Straight Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- Baltimore Orioles first baseman Will Clark  
missed his fifth straight game with a sore elbow and could be 
headed for the disabled list for the second time this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Orioles manager Ray Miller said Clark can effectively swing the  
bat, but throwing the ball is still painful proposition. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's still barking at him,'' Miller said. ``You don't need the  
greatest of arms to play first base, but you still need to throw 
the ball.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Miller is hesitant to use Clark as a pinch hitter because then  
the Orioles won't be able to put him on the disabled list 
retroactive to Aug. 14. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'll use him if I think he can win the game in the ninth  
inning,'' Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
	Also Thursday, the Orioles announced they have extended their  
working agreement with Triple-A Rochester through next season. 
</P>
<P>
	The Orioles and Red Wings have been working together since 1961,  
the third-longest longest affiliation between a major league team 
and minor league team. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
