<HEADLINE> Canadian Man Accused of Bomb Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- A Canadian man has been charged with  
possessing explosives and soliciting an American citizen to bomb 
energy facilities in Canada and the United States, U.S. officials 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Royal Canadian Mounted Police arrested and charged  
50-year-old Alfred Heinz Reumayr on Wednesday after an 18-month 
investigation by the Mounties and the U.S. Bureau of Alcohol, 
Tobacco and Firearms, the American agency said in a release. 
</P>
<P>
	``During this investigation, no explosive devices were completed  
and the public was never in danger,'' the agency said in the 
release. The FBI and the Customs Service also joined in the 
investigation. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms obtained a federal  
arrest warrant for Reumayr from a federal court in New Mexico 
accusing him of unlawful possession of explosives. The 
investigation is still under way. 
  	   	
</P>
