<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Euro Inflation Rate at 1.1 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) - The annual inflation rate in the 11  
countries that use the euro currency rose slightly in July, the 
European Union reported Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Inflation rose from 0.9 percent in June to 1.1 percent in July.  
A year ago, the rate was 1.3 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The countries, members of the European Monetary Union, are  
Belgium, Germany, Spain, France, Ireland, Italy, Luxembourg, 
Netherlands, Austria, Portugal and Finland. 
</P>
<P>
	The rate for the 15-nation EU as a whole - including Britain,  
Sweden, Denmark and Greece - was also at 1.1 percent, up from 1.0 
percent in June. The figure for July 1998 was 1.4 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Economists said the European Central Bank is unlikely to be  
concerned about the gradual rise in euro zone inflation and won't 
tighten rates until next year. 
</P>
<P>
	Inflation has been down in the euro zone because of low  
commodity prices, deregulation and price competition. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
