<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Trade Balance Year-by-Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	U.S. trade balance in merchandise and services. A minus sign  
means the country ran a deficit for that year and a plus sign shows 
a trade surplus. The figure for 1999 is an estimate based on 
results so far this year. 
</P>
<P>
	1999: -$236 billion estimate  
</P>
<P>
	1998: -$164.3 billion  
</P>
<P>
	1997: -$104.7 billion  
</P>
<P>
	1996: -$108.6 billion  
</P>
<P>
	1995: -$99.9 billion  
</P>
<P>
	1994: -$100.9 billion  
</P>
