<HEADLINE> F-15 Hits Plane and Then Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- A military jet crashed Thursday after touching  
another F-15 during a routine training mission, forcing one of the 
pilots to eject. 
</P>
<P>
	Capt. Richard W. Wedan ejected and was being treated at Ft.  
Leonard Wood Hospital. Military officials reported he did not have 
major injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident happened about 3 p.m. in Shannon County in  
south-central Missouri. Wedan's plane went down in a heavily wooded 
area. 
</P>
<P>
	The second pilot managed to fly to Lambert Airport and was not  
injured. Both planes are part of the 131st Fighter Wing of the 
Missouri Air National Guard. 
</P>
<P>
	Col. Bob Edmonds said it was not known why the planes were  
flying so close to one another. 
  	   	
</P>
