<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Thursday, Aug. 19, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Alcoa Wins Bid for Reynolds  
</P>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Alcoa Inc., the world's largest maker of  
aluminum, reached agreement to acquire No. 3 Reynolds Metals Inc. 
for more than $4 billion, but disappointed Wall Street with a deal 
today that is only slightly better than its initial hostile bid. 
Shares of both companies tumbled after the agreement was announced, 
reducing the value of the all-stock transaction to $4.34 billion 
from $4.45 billion. The deal is pegged to Alcoa stock initially 
valued at $70.88 3/4 a share, which was at the bottom end of analysts' 
estimates of Reynolds' worth. By the end of trading today, Alcoa 
stock had dropped 2.5 percent, reducing the value of the offer to 
$69.09 7/8 a share. 

</P>
<P>
	Trade Deficit Continues To Swell  
</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Americans purchased foreign-made cars,  
computers and clothing at a record rate in June, catapulting the 
half-year trade deficit more than 40 percent ahead of the pace for 
1998 when the imbalance reached an all-time high. The unexpectedly 
large $24.6 billion June deficit, 16.3 percent above the May level, 
provided a sobering backdrop today to the opening of hearings by a 
congressionally appointed panel searching for solutions to 
America's trade woes. Economists told the U.S. Trade Deficit Review 
Commission that the current trends are unsustainable and if not 
reversed, could represent a serious threat to the U.S. economy. 

</P>
<P>
	Dow Ends Down 27.54 at 10,963.84  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks slumped again today as a weakening dollar  
pushed bonds lower and gave investors another reason to sell shares 
ahead of next week's expected rise in interest rates. At the close 
on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was down 27.54 at 
10,963.84, after having dropped as much as 118 points in earlier 
trading. Broader stock indicators were also down. The Standard &AMP; 
Poor's 500 index was off 10.57 at 1,322.27, and the Nasdaq 
composite index was down 36.31 at 2,621.42. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at Thursday's close:  
Dow Industrials:        10963.84  - 27.54
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1375  Declines 1616  Unchgd  539
