<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pirates' Schourek To Miss One Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Pete Schourek will miss his next scheduled  
start for the Pittsburgh Pirates because of an inflamed left 
shoulder and may go on the disabled list. 
</P>
<P>
	Schourek had a magnetic resonance imaging test on his left  
shoulder Wednesday that found nothing more severe than 
inflammation. Jimmy Anderson will start in his place Saturday 
against Arizona's Randy Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
	``It might be a while, so the DL is definitely a possibility,''  
manager Gene Lamont said before a game against the Cincinnati Reds. 
</P>
<P>
	Schourek complained of a sore shoulder following his start  
Monday night, a 9-2 loss to the Reds. Schourek lasted a season-low 
2 2-3 innings, giving up five runs, four hits and four walks. 
</P>
<P>
	Schourek returned to Pittsburgh on Tuesday night and had the MRI  
as a precaution. 
</P>
<P>
	Schourek, 30, has been bothered by elbow problems since he led  
the Reds to the NL championship series in 1995. He had surgery to 
tighten ligaments in the elbow and clean out scar tissue in July 
1996, followed by arthroscopic surgery to remove bone spurs in 
October 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	In 16 starts and eight relief appearances, he's gone 3-7 with a  
5.68 ERA. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
