<HEADLINE> S.C. Co. Cuts Newsprint Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREENVILLE, S.C. (AP) -- Bowater Inc. plans to cut newsprint  
production by at least 75,000 metric tons to reduce inventory. 
</P>
<P>
	Bowater, one of the world's largest newsprint producers, had  
already announced it would cut production by 125,000 metric tons. 
The cuts announced Thursday will be in addition to those cuts and 
will occur at several Bowater mills, mostly over the next few 
months. 
</P>
<P>
	Bowater owns or leases more than 2 million acres of timberland  
in the United States and Canada and more than 14 million acres of 
timber cutting rights in Canada. The company has eight pulp and 
paper mills in the United States, Canada and South Korea. 

  	   	
</P>
