<DOCNO> APW19990819.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 22:31:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Red Sox Ace Berates GM Before Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- After pitching a fit in the clubhouse before  
Thursday night's game against Oakland, Red Sox ace Pedro Martinez 
insisted he has no animosity toward his manager or GM and said he 
was merely ``joking around.'' 
</P>
<P>
	However, Martinez admitted he was upset there were television  
cameras waiting for him when he arrived the ballpark. Martinez was 
scratched from his scheduled start on Saturday after he broke a 
team rule by failing to arrive the ballpark at least two hours 
before the game. 
</P>
<P>
	``You guys need to let it go,'' he told reporters after  
Thursday's 6-2 loss to the Athletics. ``The clubhouse is my house. 
If you sneak into my house and I don't know who you are, I'll shoot 
you.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Shortstop Nomar Garciaparra, who was eating at a nearby table,  
said: ``Tell Pedro I'll give him the gun.'' 
</P>
<P>
	When Martinez arrived at the ballpark late on Saturday, manager  
Jimy Williams scratched him as the starting pitcher. Martinez, who 
says he was at home getting treatment for the shoulder problem that 
caused him to go on the disabled list on July 19, came on in relief 
and earned his 17th victory. 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez yelled at Boston general manager Dan Duquette in front  
of several reporters before Thursday's game, but was smiling and 
cracking jokes after the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Arriving at 4 p.m. for the 6:05 p.m. start, Martinez found  
cameras waiting for him outside the ballpark. When Duquette walked 
into the clubhouse, Martinez yelled, ``Are you here to see if I'm 
here two hours before the game? Well I am, OK?'' 
</P>
<P>
	Afterward, Martinez claimed ``we were just talking. I'm just a  
loud talker.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez (17-4) struck out 11 in seven innings, with fans  
posting pictures of clocks on the walls where they used to hang 
``K's'' to denote his strikeouts. Martinez said he didn't see them, 
but he found it funny. 
</P>
<P>
	While yelling at Duquette before the game, Martinez demanded an  
apology from Williams. But after the game, the pitcher said he 
understood he was wrong and there was no need for an apology. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm a man about it, I made a mistake,'' Martinez said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990819.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 22:31:01 </DATE_TIME>
