<HEADLINE> Key German Business Index Improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) -- A closely watched index of German  
business confidence rose in July, a new portent of recovery for 
western European economies and the 11-nation euro currency. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts said the Ifo economic institute's monthly survey  
released Thursday indicated that Germany, Europe's biggest economy, 
would soon show an upswing. 
</P>
<P>
	Last month, a much-noted rise in the Ifo index helped bolster  
the euro's rebound from its fall almost to parity with the U.S. 
dollar. 
</P>
<P>
	Munich-based Ifo tracks sentiment and prospects in western  
German manufacturing, wholesale and construction sectors. The 11 
western German states account for 90 percent of the country's 
economic output. 
</P>
<P>
	German output figures may not reflect the improvement  
immediately, but analysts said September industrial production data 
will provide proof of a solid recovery. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
