<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gore Family Heads to N.C. Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FIGURE EIGHT ISLAND, N.C. (AP) -- Vice President Al Gore and his  
family are making a return visit this summer to a private North 
Carolina Island where they vacationed two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	``They had a great time when they were here before, and they  
look forward to coming back,'' said Raleigh businessman Tom 
Hendrickson, who helped make arrangements for the Gores' trip. 
</P>
<P>
	The vice president, fresh from a presidential campaign trip to  
Iowa, was expected to arrive at Figure Eight Island on Friday and 
stay through Aug. 31. 
</P>
<P>
	The island, just north of Wrightsville Beach, offers plenty of  
privacy. Only residents, their guests and people with business on 
the island -- pizza deliverers, mail carriers and workmen -- are 
allowed across a drawbridge over the Atlantic Intracoastal 
Waterway. 
</P>
<P>
	During his last vacation there, Gore was spotted jogging,  
reading and water-skiing with his children. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
