<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Soccer Likely To Play in Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HAVANA (AP) -- The U.S. soccer team likely will play in Cuba next  
year -- almost 53 years to the day of the last game between the 
teams in Havana. 
</P>
<P>
	Former Major League Soccer commissioner Doug Logan, acting on  
behalf of the U.S. Soccer Federation, delivered a letter to the 
Cuban Football Federation on Thursday requesting home-and-home 
exhibition games. 
</P>
<P>
	``Not only was it warmly received, we've picked a day -- July  
19,'' Logan said. 
</P>
<P>
	The only time the United States played in Cuba was a 5-2 loss on  
July 20, 1947, 12 years before Fidel Castro. The Americans are 
2-1-1 against Cuba, winning the last game 3-0 on Feb. 1, 1998 at 
Oakland, Calif. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
